<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">EQ2 Enchanters are Mages with Enchanter-flavored abilities.
<br />

<br />
While it seems to be true that you cannot charm for huge amounts of damage in EQ2, your ability to deal damage in other ways is better than in EQ1 and different than the way other EQ2 Mages do damage.  Draining the Power of your enemies can also be significant since monsters can do significant amounts of damage with their Power-based combat arts and spells.
<br />

<br />
The biggest issue right now for EQ2 Enchanters (all EQ2 Mages really) is that Scouts generally outdamage Mages.  That's because it's easier to get good weapons than it is to get Adept III or Master I spells.  However, as an Enchanter, you're not as bad off as a Sorcerer or Summoner, because you have other abilities to offer a group like crowd control and the familiar good buffs like haste and clarity that groups love.
<br />

<br />
Many EQ2 Sorcerers and Summoners are in a woeful state as far as class balance is concerned.  The situation is reminiscent in many ways to the classic "Rogue vs. Wizard" imbalances of EQ1.  They could address this by making Adept III rare harvest drops more common or by giving Mages ways to quest their Adept II spells like Scouts can quest weapons that are high-quality for their level.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
